---
import BaseLayoutNav from "../layouts/BaseLayoutNav.astro";
---

<BaseLayoutNav title="About" description="A bit about me">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 w-full xl:w-3/4">
    <section>
      <div class="flex gap-10 flex-wrap justify-evenly items-center">
        <div>
          <img
            src="/me.JPG"
            alt="photo of me"
            class="w-72 rounded-xl shadow-xl"
          />
        </div>

        <div
          class="text-inherit w-full xl:w-3/4 px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 lg:py-16 lg:px-12"
        >
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">An overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            I am a passionate and versatile professional, proud to be what I
            would consider a modern-day jack of all trades within the technology
            industry. I have extensive experience in various domains, ranging
            from general managed services (MSP) operations, network
            administration/implementation, and SaaS administration to general
            web development, Python, project management, inside sales, account
            management, and day-to-day help desk work. I enjoy the challenges
            each facet brings and try my best to improve processes and learn new
            things along the way. However, my true passion lies in development,
            where I find joy in both creating and continually expanding my
            knowledge base.
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl mt-6 font-bold">About the croissant</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            A few things: I really enjoy croissants, I named the initial project/repo
            for this site 'croissant', and I was given the nickname croissant
            while I was mentoring a robotics team in highschool. The croissant
            also provides some much needed character to the upper left corner of
            this site. The link on the croissant is a YouTube video about
            croissants posted by one of my favorite food content creators.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-base-200 text-inherit rounded-3xl shadow-lg">
      <div class="px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 lg:py-16 lg:px-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Some history</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          I've been programming on and off for about 10 years now. Recently,
          I've been extremely passionate about automating laborious aspects of
          the MSP business via the creation of API wrappers/clients and various
          Python scripts. I've tried to make time to work on projects like this
          personal site but time is a hot commodity. During my time in
          University, my classes focused on more traditional programming
          concepts and I spent a lot of time writing in C, C++, and Assembly.
          Eventually, I had the opportunity to dabble in some hardware and wrote
          Arduino code for a few projects and labs. Prior to that, I spent the
          majority of my time in highschool on a FIRST robotics FRC team as a
          programmer and in Computer Science classes. Interestingly, I worked on
          more complex IoT/Hardware projects in highschool compared to the ones
          I worked on in University.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div
        class="flex gap-10 justify-center flex-wrap xl:gap-10 xl:flex-nowrap"
      >
        <section class="bg-base-200 text-inherit rounded-3xl shadow-lg">
          <div
            class="px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 lg:py-16 lg:px-12"
          >
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Hobbies</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Self hosting is a huge one. I recently moved all my files, photos,
              calendars, and contacts off of Google/Apple to a custom built
              server. It's been a fantastic learning experience for both server
              and networking knowledge and it feels good to host my own
              software. Other than that, I've gotten pretty deep into the whole
              coffee thing over the past few years. Started with pour overs,
              graduated to making cold brew, got lazy and started buying coffee
              everyday, made some friends along the way, and now I make espresso
              at home almost every morning. I also enjoy climbing - it's a great time.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="bg-base-200 text-inherit rounded-3xl shadow-lg">
          <div
            class="px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 lg:py-16 lg:px-12"
          >
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Skills</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              I have a strong working knowledge of Python, Git, GitHub Actions,
              Azure Functions and Related Infrastructure, JS, HTML, and CSS.
              Additionally, I am highly capable in any tech support/MSP
              environment that requires Azure/M365 Administration, Network
              Administration, Server Administration, or General Technical
              Support. In that same vein, I've picked up a good amount of
              knowledge and wisdom on retail specific technology and
              deployments. I can manage projects, manage accounts, and provide
              consulting as well. Separately, I think I can make fairly decent espresso now.
            </p>

          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-base-200 text-inherit rounded-3xl shadow-lg">
      <div class="px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 lg:py-16 lg:px-12">
        <div class="">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">What I've been up to</h2>

          <p class="mt-4 text-inherit">
            The majority of my past experience is in the MSP and Retail
            industries with about 6 years in each. The MSP industry is
            incredibly unique because it encompasses a massive set of
            technologies and has exposed me to almost every aspect of what it
            takes to run a modern day, best practice business.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 md:mt-16 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-primary p-3"></div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-md font-bold">Framework IT</h2>

              <h2 class="text-sm font-bold">Operations Strategist</h2>
              <h2 class="text-xs font-bold">Jan 2023 - Present</h2>

              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-inherit">
                Responsible for the administration of all internal SaaS as well
                as the initial creation, ongoing maintenance, and development of
                the Python codebase that runs business critical automation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-primary p-3"></div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-md font-bold">Framework IT</h2>

              <h2 class="text-sm font-bold">vCIO Analyst</h2>
              <h2 class="text-xs font-bold">Jan 2021 - Jan 2023</h2>

              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-inherit">
                Transformed the internal sales process and implemented various
                changes to make the process cleaner and more efficient. Quoted
                countless of sales requests and ultimately managed the related
                project. Occasionally completed the project myself.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-primary p-3"></div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-md font-bold">Framework IT</h2>
              <h2 class="text-sm font-bold">Systems Analyst</h2>
              <h2 class="text-xs font-bold">Jan 2018 - Jan 2021</h2>

              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-inherit">
                Strong force on the help desk. Provided exceptional support to
                clients and worked with peers to learn from and solve complex
                issues. Developed an in-house web app to automate an Excel based
                process. (WordPress, PHP, SQL).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-primary p-3"></div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-md font-bold">Arc'teryx</h2>

              <h2 class="text-sm font-bold">Product Guide & Key Holder</h2>
              <h2 class="text-xs font-bold">Aug 2016 - Mar 2022</h2>

              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-inherit">
                Provided exceptional service to everyone that entered my store.
                Was responsible for opening / closing and acting as floor
                manager when needed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-primary p-3"></div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-md font-bold">
                University of Illinois at Chicago
              </h2>

              <h2 class="text-sm font-bold">Coursework towards a BS in CS</h2>
              <h2 class="text-xs font-bold">Sep 2016 - Jan 2018</h2>

              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-inherit">
                Program Design I & II (111 & 141), Mathematical Foundations of Computation (151), Programming Practicum (211), Data Structures (251), Machine Organization (261), Languages and Automata (301), and Computer Design (362)
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayoutNav>
